<p><a name="In_popular_culture" id="In_popular_culture"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Marshall_Plan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: In popular culture">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">In popular culture</span></h2>
<p><a href="/wiki/Secretary_of_Commerce" title="Secretary of Commerce" class="mw-redirect">Secretary of Commerce</a> <a href="/wiki/W._Averell_Harriman" title="W. Averell Harriman">W. Averell Harriman’s</a> press aide, <a href="/wiki/Alfred_Friendly" title="Alfred Friendly">Alfred Friendly</a>, wrote a humorous <a href="/wiki/Operetta" title="Operetta">operetta</a> about the Marshall Plan during its first year; one of the lines in the operetta was: "Wines for Sale; will you swap / A little bit of steel for <a href="/wiki/Ch%C3%A2teauneuf-du-Pape_AOC" title="Châteauneuf-du-Pape AOC">Chateau Neuf du Pape</a>?"<sup id="cite_ref-McKenzie_90-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-McKenzie-90" title=""><span>[</span>91<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="See_also" id="See_also"></a></p>
