<li>The E.R.P. was recently used as the main motif for a high value commemorative coin: the <a href="/wiki/Euro_gold_and_silver_commemorative_coins_(Austria)#2003_coinage" title="Euro gold and silver commemorative coins (Austria)">20 euro Post-War Period coin</a>, minted on September 17, 2003. The reverse side of the coin is based on the design of two famous posters of the era: the “Four in a Jeep” and the E.R.P. The German inscription “Wiederaufbau in Österreich” translates as “Reconstruction in Austria”, one of the countries aided by this program.</li>
